> Isn't it combustion that forces the piston to move. If this 
combustion
> continued in the exhaust imagine what the emisions levels would
> be.

Subaru had special stainless inserts in the exhaust ports to withstand 
the added heat from the air injection, which burned off the leftover 
hydrocarbons.  Combusting the exhaust lowers the levels.

I suspect that VW was doing the same things and went to stainless 
pipes to get reasonable life.

George
